Program: Outlook
Title: 14/03/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00pdhms
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 15 Mar 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, the librarian who risked his life to smuggle priceless antique books to safety during the siege of Sarajevo. Also, the Indian man haunted for ten years by a news photograph which captured his terror during the Gujarat riots. And the man behind the family circus that survived persecution in former East Germany. Show less